23enum class RegExpCompilationTarget : int { kBytecode, kNative };

25// TODO(jgruber): Do not expose in regexp.h.
26// TODO(jgruber): Consider splitting between ParseData and CompileData.
27struct RegExpCompileData {
28 // The parsed AST as produced by the RegExpParser.
29 RegExpTree* tree = nullptr;
30
31 // The compiled Node graph as produced by RegExpTree::ToNode methods.
32 RegExpNode* node = nullptr;
33
34 // Either the generated code as produced by the compiler or a trampoline
35 // to the interpreter.
36 Handle<Object> code;
37
38 // True, iff the pattern is a 'simple' atom with zero captures. In other
39 // words, the pattern consists of a string with no metacharacters and special
40 // regexp features, and can be implemented as a standard string search.
41 bool simple = true;
42
43 // True, iff the pattern is anchored at the start of the string with '^'.
44 bool contains_anchor = false;
45
46 // Only set if the pattern contains named captures.
47 // Note: the lifetime equals that of the parse/compile zone.
48 ZoneVector<RegExpCapture*>* named_captures = nullptr;
49
50 // The error message. Only used if an error occurred during parsing or
51 // compilation.
52 RegExpError error = RegExpError::kNone;
53
54 // The position at which the error was detected. Only used if an
55 // error occurred.
56 int error_pos = 0;
57
58 // The number of capture groups, without the global capture \0.
59 int capture_count = 0;
60
61 // The number of registers used by the generated code.
62 int register_count = 0;
63
64 // The compilation target (bytecode or native code).
65 RegExpCompilationTarget compilation_target;
66};

68class RegExp final : public AllStatic {
69 public:
70 // Whether the irregexp engine generates interpreter bytecode.
71 static bool CanGenerateBytecode();
72
73 // Verify that the given flags combination is valid.
74 V8_EXPORT_PRIVATE static bool VerifyFlags(RegExpFlags flags);
75
76 // Verify the given pattern, i.e. check that parsing succeeds. If
77 // verification fails, `regexp_error_out` is set.
78 template <class CharT>
79 static bool VerifySyntax(Zone* zone, uintptr_t stack_limit,
80 const CharT* input, int input_length,
81 RegExpFlags flags, RegExpError* regexp_error_out,
82 const DisallowGarbageCollection& no_gc);
83
84 // Parses the RegExp pattern and prepares the JSRegExp object with
85 // generic data and choice of implementation - as well as what
86 // the implementation wants to store in the data field.
87 // Returns false if compilation fails.
88 V8_WARN_UNUSED_RESULT static MaybeHandle<Object> Compile(
89 Isolate* isolate, Handle<JSRegExp> re, Handle<String> pattern,
90 RegExpFlags flags, uint32_t backtrack_limit);
91
92 // Ensures that a regexp is fully compiled and ready to be executed on a
93 // subject string. Returns true on success. Throw and return false on
94 // failure.
95 V8_WARN_UNUSED_RESULT static bool EnsureFullyCompiled(Isolate* isolate,
96 Handle<JSRegExp> re,
97 Handle<String> subject);

104 enum class ExecQuirks {
105 kNone,
106 // Used to work around an issue in the RegExpPrototypeSplit fast path,
107 // which diverges from the spec by not creating a sticky copy of the RegExp
108 // instance and calling `exec` in a loop. If called in this context, we
109 // must not update the last_match_info on a successful match at the subject
110 // string end. See crbug.com/1075514 for more information.
111 kTreatMatchAtEndAsFailure,
112 };
113
114 // See ECMA-262 section 15.10.6.2.
115 // This function calls the garbage collector if necessary.
116 V8_EXPORT_PRIVATE V8_WARN_UNUSED_RESULT static MaybeHandle<Object> Exec(
117 Isolate* isolate, Handle<JSRegExp> regexp, Handle<String> subject,
118 int index, Handle<RegExpMatchInfo> last_match_info,
119 ExecQuirks exec_quirks = ExecQuirks::kNone);
120
121 V8_EXPORT_PRIVATE V8_WARN_UNUSED_RESULT static MaybeHandle<Object>
122 ExperimentalOneshotExec(Isolate* isolate, Handle<JSRegExp> regexp,
123 Handle<String> subject, int index,
124 Handle<RegExpMatchInfo> last_match_info,
125 ExecQuirks exec_quirks = ExecQuirks::kNone);
126

173// Uses a special global mode of irregexp-generated code to perform a global
174// search and return multiple results at once. As such, this is essentially an
175// iterator over multiple results (retrieved batch-wise in advance).
176class RegExpGlobalCache final {
177 public:
178 RegExpGlobalCache(Handle<JSRegExp> regexp, Handle<String> subject,
179 Isolate* isolate);
180
181 ~RegExpGlobalCache();
182
183 // Fetch the next entry in the cache for global regexp match results.
184 // This does not set the last match info. Upon failure, nullptr is
185 // returned. The cause can be checked with Result(). The previous result is
186 // still in available in memory when a failure happens.
187 int32_t* FetchNext();
188
189 int32_t* LastSuccessfulMatch();
190
191 bool HasException() { return num_matches_ < 0; }
192
193 private:
194 int AdvanceZeroLength(int last_index);
195
196 int num_matches_;
197 int max_matches_;
198 int current_match_index_;
199 int registers_per_match_;
200 // Pointer to the last set of captures.
201 int32_t* register_array_;
202 int register_array_size_;
203 Handle<JSRegExp> regexp_;
204 Handle<String> subject_;
205 Isolate* isolate_;
206};

208// Caches results for specific regexp queries on the isolate. At the time of
209// writing, this is used during global calls to RegExp.prototype.exec and
210// @@split.
211class RegExpResultsCache final : public AllStatic {
212 public:
213 enum ResultsCacheType { REGEXP_MULTIPLE_INDICES, STRING_SPLIT_SUBSTRINGS };
214
215 // Attempt to retrieve a cached result. On failure, 0 is returned as a Smi.
216 // On success, the returned result is guaranteed to be a COW-array.
217 static Tagged<Object> Lookup(Heap* heap, Tagged<String> key_string,
218 Tagged<Object> key_pattern,
219 Tagged<FixedArray>* last_match_out,
220 ResultsCacheType type);
221 // Attempt to add value_array to the cache specified by type. On success,
222 // value_array is turned into a COW-array.
223 static void Enter(Isolate* isolate, Handle<String> key_string,
224 Handle<Object> key_pattern, Handle<FixedArray> value_array,
225 Handle<FixedArray> last_match_cache, ResultsCacheType type);
226 static void Clear(Tagged<FixedArray> cache);
227
228 static constexpr int kRegExpResultsCacheSize = 0x100;
229
230 private:
231 static constexpr int kStringOffset = 0;
232 static constexpr int kPatternOffset = 1;
233 static constexpr int kArrayOffset = 2;
234 static constexpr int kLastMatchOffset = 3;
235 static constexpr int kArrayEntriesPerCacheEntry = 4;
236};
